# Copy this file to `.env` and edit. `just` auto-loads `.env` from the repo
# root. The actual `.env` is gitignored.
#
# Code-signing identity used by xcodebuild. Defaults to "-" (ad-hoc) when this
# variable is unset, which is fine for casual development but causes the
# cdhash to change on every rebuild — invalidating macOS Accessibility grants
# and requiring you to toggle Fiti off-and-on in System Settings after each
# build. Set this to a stable identity to make grants persist across rebuilds.
#
# To list identities on your machine:
#   security find-identity -v -p codesigning
#
# Examples:
#   FITI_CODE_SIGN_IDENTITY="Developer ID Application: Your Name (TEAMID)"
#   FITI_CODE_SIGN_IDENTITY="Apple Development: Your Name (TEAMID)"
#   FITI_CODE_SIGN_IDENTITY="my-self-signed-cert-name"   # if you created one
#
# Leave commented out (or set to "-") to keep ad-hoc signing.
#FITI_CODE_SIGN_IDENTITY=
